text: More casual players don’t like saccing particularly just for ramp, and quite a few decks aren’t built for it either
Seems great in something like Kresh or Mazarek

Saccing also is a bit different in edh and I think people sometimes overlook that. In other formats saccing a thing to play a bigger thing faster wins games. Commander it isn’t as effective necessarily.
I'm thinking of picking it up for Mazirek, yeah.
The more colors you're in, the harder it is to run.
Natural Order is a great card for example but when you get that Vorinclex there’s 3x or 4x chances for it to eat a StP
Well...yes. Is that a similar scenario to Adnate?
Losing a thing to ramp a thing but I guess you’re not losing Adnate so it’s not a 2v1 but you also must have the better thing you want ramped in hand.
It’s a good card don’t get me wrong but i can see a lot of decks that just don’t want it
It’s backup to the [[spine of ish sha]] combo otherwise nope.
